title: Battersea Power Station
overview: Peter moves in with his long-term boyfriend Lloyd and tries to keep the nature of their relationship a secret from his visiting family. His mother is overbearing and conservative, while his brother, Paul, knows more than he is letting on. But a simple note written on the back of a postcard will reveal all.

title: I Was Not Born a Mistake
overview: Yaakov Smith was an ultra-orthodox married man with six children and a pillar of his community, when he left his family, his community, and Israel. It took him 20 years to return - only this time as an observant woman. The documentary by Rachel Rusinek and Eyal Ben Moshe touches honestly and openly on a subject that is both relevant and unspoken. It is also a film about self-acceptance, compassion, love, and family.

title: Chaal Gazab Hai
overview: Chaal Gazab Hai is an Indian short musical film directed by Sagar Joshi and produced by Laxman Singh Rajput which was released by Zee Music Company. The musical drama stars Jannat Zubair Rahmani and Shivam Roy Prabhakar in the lead. Theme of the drama was sung by bollywood singers Pawni Pandey and Prince Yadav.

title: Descent into the Maelstrom
overview: A stunning film based on majestic music based on a mesmerizing short story based on a unique natural phenomenon  In 1980, Philip Glass wrote a piece of music inspired by Edgar Allan Poe’s short story A Descent into the Maelstrom, which in turn was inspired by Moskenesstraumen – a unique natural phenomenon outside the Lofoten islands. In this documentary, we follow the Arctic Philharmonic Orchestra to the top of the Ryten mountain where they perform Glass’ music overlooking Moskenesstraumen itself. With its powerful music and majestic landscapes, Descent Into The Maelstrom is an ode to the beauty and harsh living conditions of Northern Norway.

title: Encounter in the Air
overview: Blerim, an employee of a TV station, takes on a highly unusual side gig - one that immerses him in a world of mental illness, paranoia, and blurred reality.

title: Wind and Water Balloons
overview: Imagine finding out that your small hometown is the only place in the world with an annual bizarre tradition. An investigation into its origin uncovers claims of discrimination and racism in the wake of disaster in 2011. This inspiring story is proof that it takes more than a couple of tornadoes to destroy the fierce loyalty and relentless pride of the balloon-flinging Blue Devils of Cordova, AL.

title: Luperca Returns
overview: Luperca has lost her way. After years of being in control and on the prowl, her sense of dominance has diminished significantly. Her powers drained, she lives a mundane existence. A commoner amidst the world of prey she once knew. Suddenly, a stranger arrives with promises of reviving her former self. Someone with the possibility of reinvigorating Luperca's dominance. But, at a cost... In the process, true intentions are revealed and Luperca fights back to reclaim what is hers.

title: Swipe
overview: A girl finds out that she has a match on a dating app with a stranger, despite swiping him to the left moments ago. She starts to fear that the man is dangerously close to her.

original_title: Scandale Epstein : le prince et le milliardaire

overview: Mark and Sophie plan to rob a post office but as things go awry, they each discover what they're really made of.

title: Illuminate - Oriana Fallaci
overview: Life and Death of Oriana Fallaci: the greatest Italian journalist of all time who made men of power tremble with her interviews and her sharp writing.

overview: Somewhere in the mountains, a man lives alone in a disappearing village. Wandering through the misty nature, interpreting among the walls of his dark houses, on the very ground with his destiny to belong to a world that has been rejected.

title: Vera
overview: After a booze-fueled fling with an older American businessman, a young Russian woman, decides to follow him back to the States under the guise of starting a relationship.

title: Father Father
overview: Father James must decide what kind of a "Father" God wants him to be?

title: Anna Nicole
overview: She left school at 14, married at 17, divorced at 26, then became a striper and married a billionaire. But she lost all when her husband died. However, when she won 450 million judgement, she became a reality show star. However, when her judgement was overruled by a Texas court, she fell on hard time and met her third husband. Her 20 year old son died then she died. Do you know who did it?

overview: A chronic procrastinator meets an otherworldly being responsible for giving humanity its great ideas.

title: Torching the Dusties
overview: Protesters have appeared outside the gates of Ambrosia Manor. From behind strange baby-faced masks, they issue a chilling simple demand: it's time for the residents of this posh retirement home to give up their space on earth.

title: Birth of the Cy-Hawk
overview: A  Local Iowa  documentary about the history of trophy  to the Cy-Hawk games.

title: Prison for Profit
overview: The Mangaung Prison opened in 2001 as South Africa’s first privately run penitentiary. Its operator, the multi-billion-dollar British security firm G4S, promised the most humane treatment and the best facilities for its nearly 3,000 prisoners—and naturally at the lowest cost.  Testimonials from whistleblowers and former prisoners, and the findings of investigative journalist Ruth Hopkins expose the reality of prison privatization. Guards are underpaid, overworked and fear every day for their lives. Prisoners are a source of income, so rehabilitation isn’t a priority. Prison for Profit shows how this profit maximization system works, and what happens when governmental tasks like detention are outsourced to powerful international corporations. And what are the negative consequences for society at large?

title: Only Love Can Do This to Me
original_title: Only Love Can Do This to Me
overview: The doctor of physics, Chen Ding, couldn't figure out. After talking about his first girlfriend for five years, why did he suddenly break up and decided to rush away thousands of miles to save it. He happened to meet Xiao Wei, an ancient Chinese girl. A car, two people, five days together, the invasion of handsome backpacker Johnson made the journey even more thrilling. Chen Ding and Xiao Wei gradually became acquainted with each other as they became accustomed to each other. At this moment, Chen Ding met his girlfriend ...

overview: Videoclip for "Ach so gern" by the German-Swedish metal duo Lindemann.

overview: The 24 year old midwife student Hanna and her boyfriend Andreas live happily together. Hanna's life is thereby turned upside down when she finds out that she's pregnant.

overview: 1907, Massachusetts. A scholar drifts from his path and finds himself in a house he assumed to be deserted - apart from a beguiling book containing dark secrets that exerts a powerful hold over those who come into contact with it.

title: Innamorarsi
overview: Elena and Pietro live in an isolated house. They live together but Pietro keeps a secret and when Elena knows it, he has to conquer her love again.

overview: Naji decides with his friends to go on holiday to a mountainous region, they face many funny and strange comedy situations ,but unexpected moment happened turned their funny journey to horror, fear and mystery.

overview: Juniper, a young woman struggling with career anxiety, must confront a secret she's hidden for over a decade.

overview: Jesus, an old man who has been a field worker and now only has his puppy left is obliged to separate from him to undertake the final stretch of his life.

But her sister’s death disturbs her daily life, triggering irrational thoughts despite her scientific and pragmatic spirit.

overview: A coming-of-age short film about one day of a boy's hunting journey.

This documentary shows how three teens cope with losing their school, home and even family members. Besides the great loss, there is also time for fun.

title: Aube

original_title: Léonard de Vinci : Le chef-d'oeuvre redécouvert

title: I'm Moshanty. Do You Love Me?
original_title: I'm Moshanty. Do You Love Me?
overview: I'm Moshanty. Do You Love Me? is a musical profile of the late South Pacific recording artist and transgender activist Moses "Moshanty" Tau and members of the LGBTQI community of Papua/New Guinea.
